---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Flight School Friend"
  description="Read the Flight School Friend privacy policy, including how prototype forms, analytics, and future email captures may be handled."
>
  <section class="bg-white max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="mb-12 border-b border-slate-200 pb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest">Last updated: June 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12 guide-content">
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Flight School Friend is an independent educational resource for future pilots. This Privacy Policy explains what information may be collected when you use the site, how it may be used, and what choices you have.</p>

      <div>
        <h2>Information we may collect</h2>
        <p>Depending on which features are live, Flight School Friend may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email address if you choose to request a checklist, roadmap, guide, or update</li>
          <li>Quiz answers and result type, if analytics or personalization are enabled</li>
          <li>Basic website analytics such as page views, clicks, device/browser information, and referral sources</li>
          <li>Messages or information you voluntarily submit through contact forms or feedback forms</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>How we may use information</h2>
        <p>We may use information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Send requested roadmaps, checklists, guides, or updates</li>
          <li>Improve the Flight School Decision Tool and future planning tools</li>
          <li>Understand which pages, tools, and guides are useful</li>
          <li>Diagnose technical issues</li>
          <li>Respond to questions or feedback</li>
          <li>Measure organic, community, and paid traffic performance</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Analytics and tracking</h2>
        <p>Flight School Friend may use analytics tools such as Google Analytics 4, Google Tag Manager, and Microsoft Clarity to understand how visitors use the site. These tools may collect usage data such as pages visited, clicks, scroll behavior, browser information, approximate location, and session recordings or heatmaps where enabled.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Email and lead capture</h2>
        <p>If you enter your email to request a roadmap, checklist, or guide, your email may be used to send that resource and occasional related flight school planning content. You should be able to unsubscribe from future emails when email functionality is live.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Third-party links</h2>
        <p>Flight School Friend may link to external resources such as FAA pages, eCFR references, aviation medical examiner resources, scholarship providers, flight schools, or other aviation websites. Flight School Friend is not responsible for the privacy practices or content of third-party websites.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Children and teens</h2>
        <p>Some flight school research may involve teens or parents helping a teen explore aviation. Flight School Friend is not intended to knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. Parents or guardians should supervise use by minors.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Data selling</h2>
        <p>Flight School Friend does not intend to sell personal information. If the business model changes, this policy should be updated before any such practice begins.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>For privacy questions, contact:<br />
        <a href="mailto:hello@flightschoolfriend.com" class="text-sky-600 hover:underline">hello@flightschoolfriend.com</a></p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>This policy may be updated as Flight School Friend adds live forms, analytics, email tools, directories, or paid products.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
      <a href="/" class="px-6 py-3 bg-slate-100 hover:bg-slate-200 text-slate-700 font-bold rounded-lg transition text-center">Return to Flight School Friend</a>
      <a href="/flight-school-decision-tool/quiz/" class="px-6 py-3 bg-sky-600 hover:bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold rounded-lg transition text-center">Start Here</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
